@startuml
title EVS cp2nus Electricity Top-Up Flow

actor User
participant "Telegram Bot\n(bot.js)" as Bot
participant "WebApp UI\n/webapp" as WebApp
participant "Express Backend\n(cp2nus router)" as Backend
participant "EVS API\np-1.evs.com.sg" as EVS
participant "eNETS Payment Page\nenetspp-nus-live.evs.com.sg" as ENETSpp
participant "NETS API\nwww2.enets.sg" as NETS
participant "ORE API\nore.evs.com.sg" as ORE

== Telegram bot flow ==
User -> Bot: /topup
Bot -> User: Ask hostel, meter ID, amount
User -> Bot: Submit selections
Bot -> User: Show WebApp button
User -> WebApp: Open Pay Now

== WebApp loading ==
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp?txtMtrId&txtAmount
Backend -> ORE: getMeterSummary(meterId)
ORE --> Backend: { address, credit_bal }
Backend --> WebApp: Loading page with meter summary

== Purchase bootstrap ==
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/bootstrap?txtMtrId&txtAmount

note over Backend: runBootstrap()

note over Backend #LightYellow: step: meter_system_check
Backend -> EVS: POST /EVSWebPOS/loginServlet (cp2 guard check)
note right: isCp2Meter() — if meter belongs\nto cp2 system, return WRONG_SYSTEM error
EVS --> Backend: valid/invalid

note over Backend #LightYellow: step: init_pay
Backend -> EVS: POST /enets/init_pay\n{ username: meterId, amount, user_id: "5771" }
EVS --> Backend: { txn_identifier, req, sign }

note over Backend #LightYellow: step: meter_info
Backend -> ORE: getMeterSummary(meterId)
ORE --> Backend: meter_info → buildPayDisplayAddress()\n(block, level, unit, building, tail)

note over Backend #LightYellow: step: enetspp_pay — fetchNetsFields()
note over Backend: buildEnetsPayUrl()\nbase64-encode m/a/d/t/s into /pay?p=
Backend -> ENETSpp: GET /pay?p=<base64(m,a,d,t,s)>
ENETSpp --> Backend: HTML with txnReq (JSON), keyId, hmac

note over Backend #LightYellow: step: callTxnReqListener()
Backend -> NETS: POST /GW2/TxnReqListener\n(txnReq JSON)\nHeaders: Hmac, Keyid
NETS --> Backend: msg: { rsaModulus, rsaExponent,\nnetsTxnRef, netsMid (UMID_xxx),\npaymtNetsMid (acquiring MID),\nmerchantTxnRef, txnRand,\nrouteTo, keyId (apiKey), hmac }

note over Backend: createPaymentSession()\nstores { txtMtrId, txtAmount, address, balance,\nnets: { rsaModulus, rsaExponent, netsTxnRef,\nnetsMid, paymtNetsMid, merchantTxnRef,\ntxnRand, keyId, hmac }, status: "pending" }\nreturns opaque token

Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, redirectUrl: "/cp2nus/webapp/pay?token=<token>" }

== Card entry ==
note over WebApp: Client-side redirect\nwindow.location.href = redirectUrl
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/pay?token=<token>
note over Backend: getPaymentSession(token)\nreads all NETS fields from session\npaymtNetsMid passed as netsMid to card page
Backend --> WebApp: Card payment page\n(loads eNETS RSA scripts from www.enets.sg)

User -> WebApp: Enter name, email, card no., exp MM/YY, CVV
note over WebApp: RSA encrypt (cardNo + cvv)\nusing rsaModulus/rsaExponent from session\nexpiryYear sent as 4-digit ("20" + YY)

WebApp -> Backend: POST /webapp/enets_pay\n(enc, netsMid=paymtNetsMid, netsTxnRef,\nmerchantTxnRef, txnRand, keyId, hmac,\nname, expiryMonth, expiryYear, consumerEmail,\nbrowserInfo..., token)

== Payment processing ==
note over Backend: getPaymentSession(token)\nreads meterId, amount, address, balance

note over Backend: step 4a: fetchEnvJsp() — seed JSESSIONID
Backend -> NETS: GET /GW2/pluginpages/env.jsp
NETS --> Backend: Set-Cookie: JSESSIONID (env session)

note over Backend: step 4b: callCreditInit() — establish credit session
Backend -> NETS: POST /GW2/credit/init;jsessionid=...\n(txnRand, paymentMode=CC_1, routeTo=FEH)
NETS --> Backend: Set-Cookie: JSESSIONID (credit session)

note over Backend: step 4c: submitPanForm()\nnetsMid used here = paymtNetsMid\n(acquiring MID from paymtSvcInfoList[0]),\nnot the top-level UMID_xxx
Backend -> NETS: POST /GW2/credit/panSubmitForm\n(enc, netsMid=paymtNetsMid, txnRand,\nname, expiryMonth, expiryYear (4-digit),\nconsumerEmail, browserInfo, ...)
NETS --> Backend: HTML: message (JSON), hmac, KeyId,\npost_form action URL

== Result path ==
alt netsTxnStatus resolved in panSubmitForm message
    note over Backend: preParsed: parse message JSON\nnetsTxnStatus "0" = success,\n"1" or ss="0" = failure\nupdate session: { status, merchantTxnRef }
    Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, status, reason,\nmerchantTxnRef, source: "pan_result" }

else POST to b2s (action URL from post_form)
    Backend -> EVS: POST /enets/b2s (or action URL)\n(message, hmac, KeyId)
    EVS --> Backend: 303 redirect →\n/pay_result?r=&t=&a=&x=&s=&m=\n(all base64-encoded)
    note over Backend: parsePayResult()\nbase64-decode r(result), t(meterId),\na(amount), x(txnRef), s(stageCode),\nm(message)\nFallback: HTML scrape if URL parse fails\nupdate session: { status, merchantTxnRef }
    Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, status, merchantTxnRef,\nmeterId, amount, reason,\nsource: "pay_result" }
end

== Final UI ==
note over WebApp: Client-side redirect\nwindow.location.href = "/cp2nus/webapp/result?token=<token>"
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/result?token=<token>
note over Backend: getPaymentSession(token)\nreads status, merchantTxnRef, meterId,\namount, reason, address, balance
Backend --> WebApp: renderFinalResultPage()

alt success
    WebApp --> User: Top-Up Successful ✅
else failure
    WebApp --> User: Top-Up Failed ⚠️
end

@enduml
